Type: Package
Package: slideimp
Title: K-NN and Sliding Window K-NN Imputation for Numeric Data
Version: 0.5.2
Authors@R: 
    person("Hung", "Pham", , "amser.hoanghung@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8271-9355"))
Description: K-nearest neighbors (K-NN) imputation algorithm for numeric
    data with options for multiple imputation with predictive mean
    matching (PMM). For large numeric datasets, such as intensive
    longitudinal data or epigenomic data where features are ordered in
    columns and have local structures, a sliding window approach for
    efficient k-NN imputation that can leverage the 'bigmemory' backend to
    conserve RAM is provided. The k-NN algorithm is described in: Hastie,
    T., Tibshirani, R., Sherlock, G., Eisen, M., Brown, P. and Botstein,
    D.  (1999) <https://hastie.su.domains/Papers/missing.pdf> "Imputing
    Missing Data for Gene Expression Arrays". The PMM algorithm is
    described in Stef van Buuren (2018) <https://stefvanbuuren.name/fimd/>
    "Flexible Imputation of Missing Data".
